{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"In 1962, Buckminster Fuller"},{"time":3000,"text":"presented the particularly audacious proposal for the Geoscope."},{"time":7000,"text":"It was a 200-foot diameter geodesic sphere"},{"time":10000,"text":"to be suspended over the East River in New York City, in full view of the United Nations."},{"time":15000,"text":"It was a big idea, for sure, and it was one that he felt could truly inform"},{"time":21000,"text":"and deeply affect the decision making of this body"},{"time":25000,"text":"through animations of global data, trends"},{"time":29000,"text":"and other information regarding the globe, on this sphere."},{"time":33000,"text":"And today, 45 years later,"},{"time":36000,"text":"we clearly have no less need for this kind of clarity and perspective,"},{"time":39000,"text":"but what we do have is improved technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42000,"text":"Today we don't need one million light bulbs to create a spherical display."},{"time":45000,"text":"We can use LEDs."},{"time":47000,"text":"LEDs are smaller, they're cheaper, they're longer lasting, they're more efficient."},{"time":52000,"text":"Most importantly for this, they're faster."},{"time":54000,"text":"And this speed, combined with today's high-performance micro-controllers,"},{"time":58000,"text":"allows us to actually simulate, in this piece,"},{"time":61000,"text":"over 17,000 LEDs -- using just 64."},{"time":66000,"text":"And the way this happens is through the phenomenon of persistence of vision."},{"time":70000,"text":"But as this ring rotates at about 1,700 rpm -- that's 28 times per second."},{"time":75000,"text":"The equator's speed is actually about 60 miles per hour."},{"time":78000,"text":"There are four on-board micro-controllers"},{"time":80000,"text":"that, each time this ring rotates"},{"time":83000,"text":"it, as it passes the rear of the display,"},{"time":85000,"text":"it picks up a position signal."},{"time":87000,"text":"And from that, the on-board micro-controllers"},{"time":89000,"text":"can extrapolate the position of the ring at all points around the revolution"},{"time":94000,"text":"and display arbitrary bitmap images and animations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"But this is really just the beginning."},{"time":100000,"text":"In addition to higher resolution versions of this display,"},{"time":103000,"text":"my father and I are working on a new patent-pending design"},{"time":106000,"text":"for a fully volumetric display using the same phenomenon."},{"time":109000,"text":"It achieves this by rotating LEDs about two axes."},{"time":112000,"text":"So as you can see here, this is a, eleven-inch diameter circuit board."},{"time":115000,"text":"These blocks represent LEDs."},{"time":117000,"text":"And so you could see that as this disc rotates about this axis,"},{"time":121000,"text":"it will create a disc of light that we can control."},{"time":124000,"text":"That's nothing new: that's a propeller clock;"},{"time":126000,"text":"that's the rims that you can buy for your car."},{"time":129000,"text":"But what is new is that, when we rotate this disc about this axis,"},{"time":134000,"text":"this disc of light actually becomes a sphere of light."},{"time":137000,"text":"And so we can control that with micro-controllers"},{"time":139000,"text":"and create a fully volumetric, three-dimensional display with just 256 LEDs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Now this piece is currently in process --"},{"time":147000,"text":"due out in May -- but what we've done is we've put together a small demo,"},{"time":152000,"text":"just to show the geometric translation of points into a sphere."},{"time":156000,"text":"I've got a little video to show you,"},{"time":158000,"text":"but keep in mind that this is with no electronic control,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and this is also with only four LEDs."},{"time":164000,"text":"This is actually only about 1.5 percent of what the final display will be in May."},{"time":167000,"text":"So, take a look."},{"time":171000,"text":"And here you can see it's rotating about the vertical axis only, creating circles."},{"time":179000,"text":"And then, as the other axis kicks in,"},{"time":181000,"text":"those actually blur into a volume."},{"time":183000,"text":"And the shutter speed of the camera"},{"time":185000,"text":"actually makes it slightly less effective in this case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"But this piece is due out in May."},{"time":190000,"text":"It'll be on display at the Interactive Telecommunications Spring Show"},{"time":193000,"text":"in Greenwich Village in New York City -- that's open to the public,"},{"time":195000,"text":"definitely invite you all to come and attend -- it's a fantastic show."},{"time":199000,"text":"There are hundreds of student innovators with fantastic projects."},{"time":203000,"text":"This piece, actually, will be on display"},{"time":205000,"text":"down in the Sierra Simulcast Lounge"},{"time":207000,"text":"in the breaks between now and the end of the show."},{"time":209000,"text":"So I'd love to talk to you all, and invite you"},{"time":211000,"text":"to come down and take a closer look."},{"time":213000,"text":"It's an honor to be here. Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}